byline.contributor: Hannah Olivennes contributed reporting from London.

abstract: Burkina Faso is preparing to hold its first general election since overthrow of Pres Blaise Compaore in 2014; election was originally scheduled for October 11 but was called off after officers associated with Compaore staged coup; about 5,000 observers are being deployed to manage expected massive turnout.
lead_paragraph: Heavy turnout is expected, and observers will fan out across the West African country to guard against irregularities in presidential and parliamentary voting.

headline.main: Burkina Faso, a Year After Uprising, Will Head to Polls
